13 (b)] The Department, in consultation with stakeholders, shall identify up–to–date,
14 evidence–based, written information about perinatal [mood and anxiety disorders]
15 MENTAL HEALTH CONDITIONS that:
16 (1) Has been reviewed by medical experts and national and local
17 organizations specializing in maternal mental health;
18 (2) Is designed for use by health care providers and pregnant and
19 postpartum women and their families;
20 (3) Is culturally and linguistically appropriate for potential recipients of
21 the information; and
22 (4) Includes:
23 (i) Information addressing:
24 1. The signs and symptoms of perinatal mood and anxiety
25 disorders;
26 2. Perinatal medication usage;
27 3. Risk factors of perinatal [mood and anxiety disorders]
28 MENTAL HEALTH CONDITIONS, including perinatal loss and high–risk pregnancy;

8 SENATE BILL 891
1 4. How and when to screen for symptoms of perinatal [mood
2 and anxiety disorders] MENTAL HEALTH CONDITIONS;
3 5. Brief intervention strategies; and
4 6. Evidence–based psychosocial treatments; and
5 (ii) Contact information for national and local maternal mental
6 health programs and services.
