1 Article – Health Occupations
2 1–231.
3 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO AN APPLICANT WHO EVALUATES AND
4 MANAGES PREGNANCY OR POSTPARTUM CARE WHILE ACTING WITHIN THE SCOPE OF
5 THE APPLICANT’S LICENSE OR CERTIFICATE.
6 (B) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, AN
7 APPLICANT FOR THE RENEWAL OF A LICENSE OR CERTIFICATE ISSUED BY A HEALTH
8 OCCUPATIONS BOARD UNDER THIS ARTICLE WHO INTERACTS WITH THE PERINATAL
9 POPULATION SHALL PROVIDE SATISFACTORY DOCUMENTATION WITH THE
10 RENEWAL APPLICATION THAT THE APPLICANT HAS COMPLETED AT LEAST TWO
11 CONTINUING EDUCATION CREDIT HOURS ON PERINATAL MENTAL HEALTH
12 CONDITIONS IDENTIFIED BY THE DEPARTMENT UNDER § 20–1803 OF THE
13 HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE.
14 (2) THE CONTINUING EDUCATION REQUIREMENT UNDER
15 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL APPLY ONLY TO AN APPLICANT’S FIRST
16 LICENSE OR CERTIFICATE RENEWAL AFTER APRIL 1, 2027.
17 (C) EACH HEALTH OCCUPATIONS BOARD MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS TO
18 CARRY OUT THIS SECTION, INCLUDING REGULATIONS SPECIFYING WHICH
19 PROVIDERS ARE SUBJECT TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
20 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 1 of this Act shall
21 apply to all policies, contracts, and health benefit plans issued, delivered, or renewed in the
22 State on or after January 1, 2027.
23 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 1 of this Act shall take
24 effect January 1, 2027.
25 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except as provided in Section
26 4 of this Act, this Act shall take effect October 1, 2026.

